geomatics.drawing.components

Class ObjectManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • geomatics.drawing.components.ObjectManager

  • public class ObjectManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The ObjectManager class stores all objects that are drawn and provides methods for adding, selecting and deleting them.
    Author:
    heol1015

      • selectAffectedToolObjects

        public void selectAffectedToolObjects(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D selection_rectangle)
        Iterates through every object of every type of geometry and calculates whether the objects lies inside the selection rectangle or outside. If the objects lies inside the selection rectangle it will be added to the ArrayList of selected objects. The function contains() is provided by Java.
        Parameters:
        selection_rectangle - Selection rectangle defined by the user

      • deleteAffectedToolObjects

        public void deleteAffectedToolObjects()
        Iterates through every object of every type of geometry in the ArrayList of the selected objects and requests the id of the objects. After that it iterates through the ArrayLists of objects that are currently displayed and deletes objects with the same id as the object in the ArrayLists of selected objects.
